{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:00Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/", "content": "Railnova is a Belgian company (Brussels) providing fleet and maintenance workflow software and telematics solutions to the railway industry. Founded in 2010. Serves blue-chip customers including Eurotunnel, Lineas, DB Cargo, SNCF, Alpha Trains. Positioned in 4bn Euro rolling stock service market.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:01Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/", "content": "Railnova offers 4 main products: (1) Railster - hardware edge device for remote monitoring and real-time data streaming, (2) Railgenius - real-time monitoring and predictive maintenance platform, (3) Railfleet - digital fleet and maintenance management platform, (4) Consulting services. Modular platform approach.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:02Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/", "content": "Railfleet core features: Real-time asset location tracking via interactive map with geofencing alerts, operational dashboard displaying fleet status/restrictions/telematic values, digital train logbook on driver tablets, centralized fleet journal for maintenance notes, digital defect reporting with photos/videos, hotline module for phone-based requests, counter reading system.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:03Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/", "content": "Railfleet maintenance planning: Maintenance planning dashboard tracking event states (unplanned, planned, overdue, closed). Intervention tracking with Gantt chart visualization for availability scheduling. Campaign management for coordinated modifications across multiple assets. Preventive maintenance auto-scheduled based on telematic counters, tolerance and time limits.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:04Z", "finding_type": "ui", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/", "content": "Railfleet visualization methods: Dashboards, interactive maps with railway focus, Gantt charts for maintenance planning and availability scheduling, notification systems. Dark theme filters visually separated from work area. Fixed position filtering at top of page or sidebar depending on page structure.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:05Z", "finding_type": "ui", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/railnova-product-update-renewed-map-with-better-focus-on-railway-and-more-customization-options/", "content": "Railnova map interface: Switched away from Google Maps to custom map with railway focus. Clear icons and consistent color scheme that blends with rest of platform. Shows train stations and workshops. The new visual structure makes workflows more intuitive with user actions at the center.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:06Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railgenius/", "content": "Railgenius features: Live dashboard with color-coded abnormality detection. Rule engine for filtered meaningful alerts. Map visualization showing alert context. GPS history module tracking routes/distance/speed. Data Inspector with customizable graph parameters. Reporting module for recurring analytics (energy, kilometers, engine hours). Fault code analysis.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:07Z", "finding_type": "ui", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railgenius/", "content": "Railgenius interface approach: Visual rule builder requiring no coding or programming. Engineers configure complex alerts through user-friendly web interface - handling thresholds, context, geographical data, event repetition, time delays. Crystallizes operational knowledge into automated detection.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:08Z", "finding_type": "tech", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railgenius/", "content": "Railgenius technical capabilities: API integration with external workflows. Cloud analytics integration (IBM Watson IoT, QlikView, Tableau, PREDIX). Real-time streaming to big data platforms. Multi-source data combination across rolling stock. Big Data Interface allows direct database access with tools like PowerBI via Snowflake.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:09Z", "finding_type": "tech", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railster/", "content": "Railster hardware connectivity: MVB, Profibus, CAN, J1708, J1939, RS232, RS485, Analog and digital I/O. Works with assets from Alstom, Bombardier, Siemens, Vossloh. Interfaces to DCPU, SIBAS, MVB, ERTMS, batteries, doors, CAT and EMD engines, fuel sensors.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:10Z", "finding_type": "tech", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/", "content": "Railfleet integration capabilities: Can be interfaced via standard web services to in-house database, ERP, asset management software or data warehouse. Supports IBM Maximo, MySQL Server, .Net, Oracle, SAP systems. Automated ML defect classification with around 96% accuracy for component identification.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:11Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/new-on-railfleet-preventive-maintenance-scheduling-precise-asset-movement-tracking-maintenance-planning-dashboard/", "content": "Railfleet preventive maintenance scheduling: Due dates automatically computed based on counter information from telematics streams. Dashboard allows planning interventions, preventive events, or corrective events based on manually reported defects. Can schedule and prepare for actual maintenance. Filter events and schedule new interventions from dashboard.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:12Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://help.railnova.eu/en/articles/10470860-unconfirmed-interventions-in-maintenance-planning-january-2025", "content": "Railfleet Unconfirmed Interventions (Jan 2025): Create interventions in 'unconfirmed' status to tentatively block time slots. Reserve time for maintenance tasks before final workshop confirmation. Better alignment between planners and workshops to reduce scheduling conflicts and last-minute rescheduling.", "relevance": "high"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:13Z", "finding_type": "pricing", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/interview-the-inside-story-on-how-the-startup-railnova-is-helping-rail-companies-transform-their-fleet-management-and-maintenance/", "content": "Railnova business model: Software as a Service (SaaS). Railnova handles server hosting, backups, software maintenance, migrations and security. Data stored securely and made available in cloud. No specific pricing disclosed publicly - enterprise customers get custom quotes based on fleet size and requirements.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:14Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/how-railnova-can-help-with-your-ecm-activities/", "content": "Railnova supports ECM (Entity in Charge of Maintenance) compliance: Helps with ECM3 fleet and maintenance management requirements. Partners collaboration tools with granular permission-based asset sharing. Multi-company solution for operators, lessors, maintainers and manufacturers.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:15Z", "finding_type": "feature", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/", "content": "Railnova supported use cases: Battery monitoring, door monitoring, fault code monitoring, HVAC monitoring, energy consumption tracking, ERTMS monitoring, automatic failure detection, condition-based maintenance. Total of 13 key use cases addressed by the platform.", "relevance": "medium"}
{"task_id": "TASK-021", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:16Z", "finding_type": "ui", "source_url": "https://www.railnova.eu/products/railfleet/", "content": "Railfleet downtime analysis: Links failures directly to fleet availability impacts. Provides visual tools to understand relationship between maintenance events and asset availability. Campaign management interface for tracking coordinated modifications across multiple assets.", "relevance": "medium"}

